data.text:
Search & Find

Most of our HCC Library Searches in one place.

Open Access Databases

Find high quality open access (free to use) databases by program/subject or format.

Accessible Resources

Whether you are a student using library resources to complete a paper, faculty creating digital handouts for a class this guide is for you.

Research Guides

The best user-friendly resources gathered by HCC librarians to help you with your research and assignments

Other Libraries

Find and use resources in other libraries.

Research & Writing

Learn to find and cite your sources, how to get started with your writing assignments, and more.

Style Guides

These resources will help you cite your sources correctly and avoid plagiarism.

Reference Sources

Use these sources for background information on your topic and for quick facts and statistics.

Plagiarism

Use these resources to understand plagiarism and how to avoid it.

Writing Skills

Hone your writing skills here. We have provided sample papers for comparison.

Locations & Hours

When and where to visit the libraries, along with contact and staffing information.

Mission, Vision & Values

Expert support for learning and teaching in the libraries and online.

Guidelines and Procedures

How many books can you check out? How are the libraries organized? Find out here.

Comments & Suggestions

Suggest a purchase, or let us know how we're doing. We want to read from you!

Library Dashboard

Visualize the scope and use of our resources and services.

Ask A Librarian

Get personal assistance from an HCC librarian or find answers in our Frequently Asked Questions.

Questions & Answers Here!

Have a question? Maybe we've already answered. Find out here.

Did We Help?

Let us know how we're doing. This is also where we assess ourselves.

Library Information For...

We strive to offer great services to each member of the HCC Community.

Librarians

Librarians use these links, but some of them are useful for HCC students and faculty, too.
